msgstr "你藏起了你的%s。"

#. ~ Use action holster_prompt for {'str_sp': 'Red Line combat vest'}.
#. ~ Use action holster_prompt for {'str_sp': '4th Reich combat vest'}.
#. ~ Use action holster_prompt for {'str_sp': 'South Gate Station security
#. vest'}.
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_armor\sgs_armor.json
msgid "Stash ammo"
msgstr "藏匿弹药"

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': 'Red Line combat vest'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"A combat vest found in common use amongst the many soldiers of the red line."
" Relatively cheap to make, its low encumberance comes at the cost of having "
"relatively little ballistic protection."
msgstr "红线众多士兵中普遍使用的战斗背心。制作相对廉价，其低负重性以较弱的弹道防护为代价。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "Soviet flag"
msgid_plural "Soviet flags"
msgstr[0] "苏联国旗"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Soviet flag'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "A large Soviet flag made to fly in even the worst conditions."
msgstr "一面大型苏联国旗，即使在最恶劣的条件下也能飘扬。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "Red Line Ushanka"
msgid_plural "Red Line Ushankas"
msgstr[0] "红线乌沙帽"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Red Line Ushanka'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"A hat made from the pelts of animals.  Extremely warm. Often worn by the "
"citizens of the Red Line."
msgstr "用动物毛皮制成的帽子。极其保暖。常被红线公民佩戴。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "4th Reich officer's hat"
msgid_plural "4th Reich officer's hats"
msgstr[0] "第四帝国军官帽"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "4th Reich officer's hat"}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"Few can be deemed pure enough to be allowed entry into the Reich Stations. "
"Even fewer can become officers with an inflated sense of self importance."
msgstr "很少有人能被认定足够纯洁以获准进入帝国车站。更少人能成为军官，并怀有膨胀的自我重要感。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "4th Reich Formal Jacket"
msgid_plural "4th Reich Formal Jackets"
msgstr[0] "第四帝国正式夹克"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '4th Reich Formal Jacket'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"An authoritative-looking jacket outfitted with a 4th Reich Armband. Common "
"amongst the higher ranking members of the 4th Reich stations."
msgstr "一件外观威严的夹克，配有第四帝国臂章。常见于第四帝国车站的高级成员中。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "4th Reich combat vest"
msgid_plural "4th Reich combat vest"
msgstr[0] "第四帝国战斗背心"

#. ~ Description for {'str_sp': '4th Reich combat vest'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"A combat vest found in common use amongst the well-trained, but somewhat "
"rare, members of the 4th Reich stations. Offers a relatively decent amount "
"of protection, at the cost of increased encumbrance."
msgstr "第四帝国车站训练有素但较为稀少的成员中普遍使用的战斗背心。提供相对不错的防护，代价是增加负重。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "4th Reich flag"
msgid_plural "4th Reich flags"
msgstr[0] "第四帝国国旗"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '4th Reich flag'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "A large Reich flag made to fly in even the worst conditions."
msgstr "一面大型帝国国旗，即使在最恶劣的条件下也能飘扬。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "4th Reich Heavy Armor"
msgid_plural "4th Reich Heavy Armors"
msgstr[0] "第四帝国重型护甲"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '4th Reich Heavy Armor'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"Found only amongst the rarest of the rare Reich troops, this armor portends "
"doom for those of the Red Line who come across it. Outfitted with thick "
"metal plates, this armor is rather heavy."
msgstr "仅在极罕见的帝国部队中发现，这件护甲预示着红线成员遭遇它时的厄运。配备厚金属板，相当沉重。"

#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid "Reich Stahlhelm"
msgid_plural "Reich Stahlhelms"
msgstr[0] "帝国钢盔"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Reich Stahlhelm'}
#: .\Metro\metro_armor\metro_armor.json
msgid ""
"A heavy steel helmet that provides excellent protection from all sorts of "
"damage.  How exactly people forced to live in the New England Metro got a "
"hold of these seemingly geniune articles is one of the great many mysteries "
"of the Cataclysm."
msgstr "一顶重型钢盔，提供出色的全方位伤害防护。被迫生活在新英格兰地铁的人们如何获得这些看似真品的头盔，是大灾变的众多谜团之一。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_pistols.json
msgid "lolife magazine"
msgid_plural "lolife magazines"
msgstr[0] "洛莱夫弹匣"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'lolife magazine'}
#. ~ Description for {'str': 'lolife extended magazine'}
#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_pistols.json
msgid ""
"A somehwat crude metal magazine for use with the common lolife pistol of the"
" metro."
msgstr "一个略显粗糙的金属弹匣，用于地铁常见的洛莱夫手枪。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_pistols.json
msgid "lolife extended magazine"
msgid_plural "lolife extended magazines"
msgstr[0] "洛莱夫扩容弹匣"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_pistols.json
msgid "Lolife"
msgid_plural "Lolife"
msgstr[0] "洛莱夫"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_pistols.json
msgid ""
"The Lolife is a metro-made semi-automatic handgun with a standard eight-"
"round magazine chambered in .44 Magnum. As the Lolife is a metro-made "
"weapon, it has very little known history. It appears that Lolife has been "
"produced since at least 2023."
msgstr ""
"洛莱夫是一款地铁制造的半自动手枪，标准八发弹匣，口径为.44马格南。由于是地铁制造的武器，其历史鲜为人知。似乎至少从2023年起就开始生产洛莱夫。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "Bastard magazine"
msgid_plural "Bastard magazines"
msgstr[0] "杂种卡宾枪弹匣"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Bastard magazine'}
#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "A crude magazine for the bastard carbine.  Holds 30 rounds."
msgstr "杂种卡宾枪的粗糙弹匣，可容纳30发子弹。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "Kalash 2012 magazine"
msgid_plural "Kalash 2012 magazines"
msgstr[0] "卡拉什2012弹匣"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Kalash 2012 magazine'}
#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid ""
"A standard magazine made for the Kalash 2012 rifle, made entirely of a "
"complex polymer.  Holds 40 rounds."
msgstr "为卡拉什2012步枪制造的标准弹匣，完全由复杂聚合物制成，可容纳40发子弹。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "Bastard"
msgid_plural "Bastards"
msgstr[0] "杂种卡宾枪"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid ""
"The Bastard was one of the first Metro-made weapons. It is considerably "
"cheaper to make and maintain than other guns, needing relatively few parts "
"to create, making it ideal for weaponsmiths with few resources. This gun, "
"like most, has its ups and downs. It has a high rate of fire and holds 30 "
"rounds of ammunition, but fares poorly for sniping due to very poor accuracy"
" beyond a few yards."
msgstr ""
"杂种卡宾枪是地铁最早制造的武器之一。与其他枪支相比，它的制造和维护成本要低得多，只需相对较少的零件即可制造，因此非常适合资源有限的武器匠。这把枪像大多数武器一样，有其优缺点。它射速高，可容纳30发弹药，但由于几码外的精度极差，不适合狙击。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_rifles.json
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_smg.json
msgid "semi-auto"
msgstr "半自动"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_rifles.json
#: .\UnderRail\underrail_weapons\sgs_smg.json
msgid "auto"
msgstr "自动"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "Kalash 2012"
msgid_plural "Kalash 2012s"
msgstr[0] "卡拉什2012"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid ""
"Kalash 2012 is one of the weapons in the Metro that predates the war and it "
"is highly prized. It's advanced polymer frame is rather unusual for Russian "
"weapons, but it seems to make a good account of itself."
msgstr "卡拉什2012是地铁中战前就存在的武器之一，备受珍视。其先进的聚合物枪身对于俄罗斯武器来说相当不寻常，但似乎表现不俗。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "2 rd."
msgstr "2发。"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid "shambler"
msgid_plural "shamblers"
msgstr[0] "蹒跚者"

#: .\Metro\metro_weapons\metro_rifles.json
msgid ""
"A shotgun modified to use a revolver cylinder mechanism, it can hold 6 "
"cartridges. Common among the denizens of the metro, and packs quite a punch."
msgstr "一种改装为使用转轮弹巢机构的霰弹枪，可容纳6发弹药。在地铁居民中很常见，威力十足。"

#: .\UnderRail\sgs_ammo.json
msgid "5mm Standard Round"
msgid_plural "5mm Standard Rounds"
msgstr[0] "5毫米标准弹"

#: .\UnderRail\sgs_ammo.json
